## Getting Started

### Step 1 — Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/dhruvd275/prediction-game-platform.git
cd prediction-game-platform
git checkout dev
```

---

### Step 2 — Set Up Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file inside the `backend/` folder:

```bash
cd backend
touch .env
```

Add the following to `.env`:

```
PORT=3000
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://pguser:pgpass@localhost:5432/prediction_game
JWT_SECRET=change_this_later
ADMIN_SECRET=supersecretkey
CRICKET_API_KEY=your_cricket_api_key
FOOTBALL_API_KEY=your_football_api_key
```

---

### Step 3 — Start the Database

```bash
# From the project root
docker compose up -d

# Verify the container is running
docker ps
```

You should see `pg_prediction_game` listed with status `Up`.

---

### Step 4 — Run Database Migrations

Run all SQL migrations in order:

```bash
docker exec -i pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game < backend/sql/001_init.sql
docker exec -i pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game < backend/sql/002_game_core.sql
docker exec -i pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game < backend/sql/003_seed_f1_event.sql
docker exec -i pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game < backend/sql/004_market_options.sql
docker exec -i pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game < backend/sql/005_credit_log.sql
docker exec -i pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game < backend/sql/006_add_username.sql
docker exec -i pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game < backend/sql/007_teams_players.sql
```

Verify tables were created:

```bash
docker exec -it pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game -c "\dt"
```

---

### Step 5 — Install Backend Dependencies and Start

```bash
cd backend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Test the backend is running:

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/health
```

Expected response: `{"status":"ok","message":"Backend is running"}`

---

### Step 6 — Install Frontend Dependencies and Start

Open a new terminal window:

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
ionic serve
```

The app will open at: `http://localhost:8100`

To access from other devices on the same WiFi:

```bash
ionic serve --external
```

