## User Management Commands

### Add Credits to a User

```bash
docker exec -it pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game -c "UPDATE users SET credits = credits + 500 WHERE email = 'test@test.com';"
```

### Set Credits to a Specific Amount

```bash
docker exec -it pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game -c "UPDATE users SET credits = 1000 WHERE email = 'test@test.com';"
```

### Top Up All Users

```bash
docker exec -it pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game -c "UPDATE users SET credits = 1000;"
```

### Reset a User Password

Step 1 — Generate bcrypt hash (run from inside `backend/` folder):

```bash
cd backend
node -e "const bcrypt = require('bcrypt'); bcrypt.hash('NewPassword123!', 10).then(h => console.log(h));"
```

Step 2 — Update in database (use single quotes around the hash):

```bash
docker exec -it pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game
```

Then inside psql:

```sql
UPDATE users SET password_hash = 'PASTE_HASH_HERE' WHERE email = 'user@example.com';
\q
```

### Change a Username

```bash
docker exec -it pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game -c "UPDATE users SET username = 'NewUsername' WHERE email = 'user@example.com';"
```

### Delete a User

```bash
docker exec -it pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game -c "DELETE FROM users WHERE email = 'user@example.com';"
```

