## API Endpoint Testing

### Health Check

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/health
```

### Register a User

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/auth/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"test@example.com","username":"testuser","password":"Test123!"}'
```

### Login

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"test@example.com","password":"Test123!"}'
```

Save the token from the response, then use it for authenticated requests:

```bash
TOKEN="your_jwt_token_here"
```

### Get Current User Info

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/me \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN"
```

### Get All Events

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/events
```

### Get Markets for an Event

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/events/1/markets
```

### Submit a Prediction

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/predictions \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  -d '{"market_id": 1, "selection": "VER", "stake": 100}'
```

### Get My Predictions

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/predictions/me \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN"
```

### Get Leaderboard

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/leaderboard
```

### Admin — Auto-Lock Past Cutoff Markets

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/markets/auto-lock \
  -H "x-admin-key: supersecretkey"
```

### Admin — Resolve a Market

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/markets/1/resolve \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "x-admin-key: supersecretkey" \
  -d '{"result": "VER"}'
```

### Admin — Get Platform Stats

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000/admin/stats \
  -H "x-admin-key: supersecretkey"
