## Troubleshooting

### Backend won't start — "Cannot find module"

```bash
cd backend
npm install
```

### Frontend won't start — "ionic: command not found"

```bash
npm install -g @ionic/cli
```

### Database connection refused

Make sure Docker is running and the container is up:

```bash
docker compose up -d
docker ps
```

### Port 3000 already in use

```bash
lsof -i :3000
kill -9 <PID>
```

### Port 8100 already in use

```bash
lsof -i :8100
kill -9 <PID>
```

### Check what Postgres thinks the time is (for timezone issues)

```bash
docker exec -it pg_prediction_game psql -U pguser -d prediction_game -c "SELECT NOW();"
```

